        "caption": "The 8 initial configurations for a triple-binary encounter. The target triple has an inner separation $a_{\\rm in} = 4$\\,au, and outer separation $a_{\\rm out} = 40$\\,au. The projectile binary with $a_{\\rm p} = 6$\\,au, encounters the terget triple with a relative velocity of $v_{\\rm enc} = 7$\\,km/s. The last four columns give the interaction cross-section ($\\sigma$), the fraction of cases in which VFTS~590 is ejected ($f_{\\rm esc, VFTS590}$), with a velocity of at least $v_{\\rm ej} \\apgt 27.6$\\,km/s ($f_{\\rm run}$), and the corresponding rate that VFTS~590 and the two surviving binaries are ejected with at least $v_{\\rm ej} \\apgt 27.6$\\,km/s calculated for the core collapsed cluster R136 ($\\Gamma_{\\rm esc, VFTS590}$). The most likely scenario is G.",
